Davon Malcolm Reed (born June 11, 1995) is an American basketball player who played college basketball for the Miami Hurricanes men's basketball team in the Atlantic Coast Conference. He was drafted by the Phoenix Suns with the 32nd pick (2nd in the 2nd round) of the 2017 NBA Draft.

A resident of Ewing Township, New Jersey, Reed played high school basketball at Princeton Day School.[1]

College career[edit]

He averaged 10.3 points and 3.6 rebounds per game throughout four seasons of playing time, with his best averages being 14.9 points and 4.8 rebounds in his last season for Miami. Reed developed a reputation as a good shooter who can defend four positions.[2] As a senior he was named to the All-Atlantic Coast Conference Third Team and All-Atlantic Coast Conference Defensive Team.[3]

Professional career[edit]

Reed was selected as the 32nd pick of the 2017 NBA Draft by the Phoenix Suns.[4] He also joined fellow rookies Josh Jackson and Alec Peters, as well as fellow teammates Dragan Bender, Marquese Chriss, Tyler Ulis, and Derrick Jones Jr. for the 2017 NBA Summer League.[5] Reed signed a four-year deal with the Suns on July 6, 2017.[6][7] In the 2017 Summer League, Reed recorded averages of 14.0 points, 4.0 rebounds, 1.2 assists, and 1.2 steals per game in the six games he played there.
